question: What is the percentage of molecules that are carcinogenic?
original_query: SELECT CAST(COUNT(CASE WHEN T.label = '+' THEN T.molecule_id ELSE NULL END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(T.molecule_id) FROM molecule t
llm_output:
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS temp;

CREATE TABLE temp AS 
SELECT COUNT(T2.molecule_id) AS carcinogenic_count, 
       ( SELECT COUNT(T1.molecule_id) 
        FROM molecule AS T1 
        UNION ALL 
        SELECT T2.molecule_id 
        FROM molecule AS T2 
        EXCEPT SELECT T1.molecule_id 
                    FROM molecule AS T1 
                    UNION ALL 
                    SELECT T2.molecule_id 
                    FROM molecule AS T2 
                    WHERE T1.label = 'carcinogenic') AS total_molecule_count
FROM (
  SELECT COUNT(T1.molecule_id) AS carcinogenic_count
  FROM molecule AS T1 
  WHERE T1.label = 'carcinogenic'
) AS T1, molecule AS T2;

SELECT ROUND(carcinogenic_count * 100.0 / total_molecule_count, 2) AS percentage FROM temp;

        EXCEPT SELECT T1.molecule_id 
                    FROM molecule AS T1 
                    UNION ALL
